Chief executive officer, Alternative Adverts Limited, Emmanuel Nwafor has urged the federal government to make deliberate commitments towards investing in digital products that will bring the expected foreign exchange and boost the National Economy. The advertising guru said government can take advantage of the viable opportunities available in the digital space to drive home its dreams of creating employment in the service sector. He disclosed this during an entrepreneurial training at the weekend in Abuja on the theme “Digital Marketing; proven strategy and method to accelerate business growth in 2020”. Mr. Nwafor added that government is the only one that can bridge the gap in the industry. Nwafor said that digital marketing has assumed high prominence in recent times, noting that a whole lot of people are beginning to appreciate innovations, technology and new ideas of doing businesses. “Even some older business owners who believe that there have been in business successfully  for decades and were satisfied with their old method of doing business but when they start seeing smaller businesses started 2 to 3 years intervals using digital tools beginning to outgrow the older businesses they started becoming receptive to digital marketing.” He said that investment in digital products could be risky, hence banks and other financial institutions whose aim is to make profits always shy away from it because they cannot risk their money. “But government can make funds available and invest in digital products,” he enthused. Nwafor said “it’s true that not all of them will succeed but if 1 or 2 of the investment succeeds and becomes a global brand it can bring the expected foreign exchange, imagine how much dollars Nigeria are spending every day on Google, facebook, instagram and others.”